ot understand.\x{201d} The young girl looked at me, her eyes colder and brighter than the winter moon. \x{201c}I am Artemis,\x{201d} she said. \x{201c}Goddess of the Hunt.\x{201d} THREE BIANCA DI ANCELO MAKES A CHOICE After seeing Dr. Thorn turn into a monster and plummet off the edge of a cliff with Anna- beth, you'd think nothing else could shock me. But when this twelve-year-old girl told me she was the goddess Artemis, I said something real intelligent like, \x{201c}Um\x{2026} okay.\x{201d} That was nothing compared to Grover. He gasped, then knelt hastily in the snow and star- ted yammering, \x{201c}Thank you, Lady Artemis! You're so\x{2026} you're so\x{2026} Wow!\x{201d} \x{201c}Get up, goat boy!\x{201d} Thalia snapped. \x{201c}We have other things to worry about. Annabeth is gone!\x{201d} \x{201c}Whoa,\x{201d} Bianca di Angelo said. \x{201c}Hold up. Time out.\x{201d} Everybody looked at her. She pointed her finger at all of us in turn, like she was trying to connect the dots. \x{201c}Who\x{2026} who are you people?\x{201d}Artemis's expression softened.\x{201c}It might be a better question, my dear girl, to ask who are you!Who are your parents?\x{201d} Bianca glanced nervously at her brother, who was still staring in awe at Artemis. Our parents are dead,\x{201c} Bianca said. \x{201d}We're orphans. There's a bank trust that pays for our school, but\x{2026}\x{201c} She faltered. I guess she could tell from our faces that we didn't believe her. \x{201d}What?\x{201c} she demanded. \x{201d}I'm telling the truth.\x{201c} \x{201d}You are a half-blood,\x{201c} Zoe Nightshade said. Her accent was hard to place. It sounded old-fashioned, like she was reading from a really old book. \x{201d}One of thy parents was mortal. The other was an Olympian.\x{201c} \x{201d}An Olympian\x{2026} athlete?\x{201c} \x{201d}No,\x{201c} Zoe said. \x{201d}One of the gods.\x{201c} \x{201d}Cool!\x{201c} said Nico. \x{201d}No!\x{201c} Bianca's voice quavered. \x{201d}This is not cool!\x{201c} Nico danced around like he needed to use the restroom. \x{201d}Does Zeus really have lightning bolts that do six hundred damage? Does he get extra movement points for\x{2014}\x{201c} \x{201d}Nico, shut up!\x{201c} Bianca put her hands to her face. \x{201d}This is not your stupid Mythomagic game, okay? There are no gods!\x{201c} As anxious as I felt about Annabeth\x{2014}all I wanted to do was search for her\x{2014}I couldn't help feeling sorry for the di Angelos. I remembered what it was like for me when I first learned I was a demigod. Thalia must've been feeling something similar, because the anger in her eyes subsided a little bit. \x{201d}Bianca, I know it's hard to believe. But the gods are still around. Trust me. They're immortal. And whenever they have kids with regular humans, kids like us, well\x{2026} Our lives are dangerous.\x{201c} \x{201d}Dangerous,\x{201c} Bianca said, \x{201d}like the girl who fell.\x{201c} Thalia turned away. Even Artemis looked pained. \x{201d}Do not despair for Annabeth,\x{201c} the goddess said. \x{201d}She was a brave maiden. If she can be found, I shall find her.\x{201c} \x{201d}Then why won't you let us go look for her?\x{201c} I asked. \x{201d}She is gone. Can't you sense it, Son of Poseidon? Some magic is at work. I do not know exactly how or why, but your friend has vanished.\" I still wanted to jump off the cliff and search for her, but I had a feeling that Artemis was right. Annabeth was gone. If she'd been down there in the sea, I thought, I'd be able to feel her presence.\x{201c}Oo!\x{201d} Nico raised his hand. \x{201c}What about Dr. Thorn? That was awesome how you shot him with arrows! Is he dead?\x{201d} \x{201c}He was a manticore,\x{201d} Artemis said. \x{201c}Hopefully he is destroyed for now, but monsters nev- er truly die. They re-form over and over again, and they must be hunted whenever they re- appear.\x{201d} \x{201c}Or they'll hunt us,\x{201d} Thalia said. Bianca di Angelo shivered. \x{201c}That explains\x{2