t much we know.\x{201d} \x{201c}Oh, goody!\x{201d} Dionysus said. Everyone looked at him. He glanced up innocently from the pages of Wine Connoisseur magazine. \x{201c}Ah, pinot noir is making a comeback. Don't mind me.\x{201d} \x{201c}Percy is right,\x{201d} Silena Beauregard said. \x{201c}Two campers should go.\x{201d} \x{201c}Oh, I see,\x{201d} Zoe said sarcastically. \x{201c}And I suppose you wish to volunteer?\x{201d} Silena blushed. \x{201c}I'm not going anywhere with the Hunters. Don't look at me!\x{201d} \x{201c}A daughter of Aphrodite does not wish to be looked at,\x{201d} Zoe scoffed. \x{201c}What would thy mother say?\x{201d} Silena started to get out of her chair, but the Stoll brothers pulled her back. \x{201c}Stop it,\x{201d} Beckendorf said. He was a big guy with a bigger voice. He didn't talk much, but when he did, people tended to listen. \x{201c}Let's start with the Hunters. Which three of you will go?\x{201d} Zoe stood. \x{201c}I shall go, of course, and I will take Phoebe. She is our best tracker.\x{201d} \x{201c}The big girl who likes to hit people on the head?\x{201d} Travis Stoll asked cautiously. Zoe nodded. \x{201c}The one who put the arrows in my helmet?\x{201d} Connor added.. \x{201c}Yes,\x{201d} Zoe snapped. \x{201c}Why?\x{201d} \x{201c}Oh, nothing,\x{201d} Travis said. \x{201c}Just that we have a T-shirt for her from the camp store.\x{201d} He held up a big silver T-shirt that said ARTEMIS THE MOON GODDESS, FALL HUNTING TOUR 2002, with a huge list of national parks and stuff underneath. \x{201c}It's a collector's item. She was admiring it. You want to give it to her?\x{201d} I knew the Stolls were up to something. They always were. But I guess Zoe didn't know them as well as I did. She just sighed and took the T-shirt. \"As I was saying, I will takePhoebe. And I wish Bianca to go.\x{201c} Bianca looked stunned. \x{201d}Me? But\x{2026} I'm so new. I wouldn't be any good.\x{201c} \x{201d}You will do fine,\x{201c} Zoe insisted. \x{201d}There is no better way to prove thyself.\x{201c} Bianca closed her mouth. I felt kind of sorry for her. I remembered my first quest when I was twelve. I had felt totally unprepared. A little honored, maybe, but a lot resentful and plenty scared. I figured the same things were running around in Bianca's head right now. \x{201d}And for campers?\x{201c} Chiron asked. His eyes met mine, but I couldn't tell what he was think- ing. \x{201d}Me!\x{201c} Grover stood up so fast he bumped the Ping-Pong table. He brushed cracker crumbs and Ping-Pong ball scraps off his lap. \x{201d}Anything to help Artemis!\x{201c} Zoe wrinkled her nose. \x{201d}I think not, satyr. You are not even a half-blood.\x{201c} \x{201d}But he is a camper,\x{201c} Thalia said. \x{201d}And he's got a satyr's senses and woodland magic. Can you play a tracker's song yet, Grover?\x{201c} \x{201d}Absolutely!\x{201c} Zoe wavered. I didn't know what a tracker's song was, but apparently Zoe thought it was a good thing. \x{201d}Very well,\x{201c} Zoe said. \x{201d}And the second camper?\x{201c} \x{201d}I'll go.\x{201c} Thalia stood and looked around, daring anyone to question her. Now, okay, maybe my math skills weren't the best, but it suddenly occurred to me that we'd reached the number five, and I wasn't in the group. \x{201d}Whoa, wait a sec,\x{201c} I said. \x{201d}I want to go too.\x{201c} Thalia said nothing. Chiron was still studying me, his eyes sad. \x{201d}Oh,\x{201c} Grover said, suddenly aware of the problem. \x{201d}Whoa, yeah, I forgot! Percy has to go. I didn't mean\x{2026} I'll stay. Percy should go in my place.\x{201c} \x{201d}He cannot,\x{201c} Zoe said. \x{201d}He is a boy. I won't have Hunters traveling with a boy.\x{201c} \x{201d}You traveled here with me,\x{201c} I reminded her. \x{201d}That was a short-term emergency, and it was ordered by the goddess. I will not go across country and fight many dangers in the company of a boy.\x{201c} \x{201d}What about Grover?\x{201c} I demanded. Zoe shook